  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hosea\u2019s Wife and Children"
      title: "Hosea\u2019s Wife and Children"
      number: 1
      content: '  The word of the Lord that came to Hosea the son of Beeri in the
        days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz and Hezekiah, kings of Judah, and in the days
        of Jeroboam the son of Joash king of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When the Lord first spoke through Hosea, the Lord said to him, \u201CGo,
        take for yourself a wife of prostitution and have children of [her] prostitution;
        for the land commits great acts of prostitution by not following the Lord.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So he went and took Gomer the daughter of Diblaim, and she conceived
        and bore him a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the Lord said to him, \u201CName him Jezreel; for yet in a little
        while I will avenge the blood [that was shed in the Valley] of Jezreel and
        inflict the punishment for it on the house of Jehu, and I will put an end
        to the kingdom of the house of Israel. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "On that day I will break the bow [of the military power] of Israel
        in the Valley of Jezreel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then Gomer conceived again and gave birth to a daughter. And the
        Lord said to Hosea, \u201CName her Lo-Ruhamah (not shown mercy), for I will
        no longer have mercy on the house of Israel, that I would ever forgive them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But I will have mercy on the house of Judah and will rescue them
        by the Lord their God, and will not rescue them by bow, sword, war, horses,
        or horsemen.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now when Gomer had weaned Lo-Ruhamah, she conceived and gave birth
        to a son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CName him Lo-Ammi (not my people), for you
        are not My people and I am not your God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Yet the number of the sons of IsraelShall be like the sand of the
        sea,Which cannot be measured or numbered;And in the placeWhere it is said
        to them,\u201CYou are not My people,\u201DIt will be said to them,\u201CYou
        are the sons of the living God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Then the sons of Judah and the sons of Israel shall be gathered together,And
        they will appoint for themselves one leader,And they will go up from the
        land,For great and glorious will be the day of Jezreel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Unfaithfulness Condemned"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Unfaithfulness Condemned"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201C[Hosea,] say to your brothers, \u2018Ammi (you are my people),\u2019
        and to your sisters, \u2018Ruhamah (you have been pitied and have obtained
        mercy).\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Contend with your mother (nation); contend,For she is not my wife
        and I am not her husband;And have her remove her [marks of] prostitution
        from her faceAnd her adultery from between her breasts  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Or I will strip her nakedAnd expose her as on the day she was born,And
        make her like a wildernessAnd make her like a parched landAnd slay her with
        thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Also, I will have no mercy on her children,Because they are the children
        of prostitution.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For their mother has played the prostitute;She who conceived them
        has acted shamefully,For she said, \u2018I will pursue my loversWho give
        me my food and my water,My wool and my flax, my oil and my [refreshing] drinks.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore, behold, I [the Lord God] will hedge up her way with thorns;And
        I will build a wall against her [shutting off her way] so that she cannot
        find her paths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "She will [passionately] pursue her lovers, but she will not overtake
        them;And she will seek them, but will not find them.Then she will say, \u2018Let
        me go and return to my first husband,For it was better for me then than now!\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CFor she (Israel) has not noticed nor understood nor realized
        that it was I [the Lord God] who gave her the grain and the new wine and
        the oil,And lavished on her silver and gold,Which they used for Baal and
        made into his image.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore, I will return and take back My grain at harvest timeAnd
        My new wine in its season.I will also take away My wool and My flax  Given
        to cover her nakedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And now I will uncover her lewdness and shameIn the sight of her
        lovers,And no one will rescue her from My hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I will also put an end to all her rejoicing,Her feasts, her New Moons,
        her Sabbaths,And all her festivals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I will destroy her vines and her fig treesOf which she has said,
        \u2018These are my wagesWhich my lovers have given me.\u2019And I will make
        them a forest,And the animals of the open country will devour them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Restoration of Israel'
      title: Restoration of Israel
      number: 13
      content: "And I will punish her for the [feast] days of the Baals,When she
        used to offer sacrifices and burn incense to themAnd adorn herself with her
        earrings and nose rings and her jewelry,And follow her lovers, so that she
        forgot Me,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CTherefore, behold, I will allure IsraelAnd bring her into the
        wilderness,And I will speak tenderly to her [to reconcile her to Me].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then I will give her her vineyards from there,And make the Valley
        of Achor a door of hope and expectation [anticipating the time when I will
        restore My favor on her].And she will sing there and respond as in the days
        of her youthAs in the day when she came up from the land of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "It shall come about in that day,\u201D says the Lord,\u201CThat you
        will call Me Ishi (my husband)And will no longer call Me Baali (my Baal).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For I will remove the names of the Baals from her mouth,So that they
        will no longer be mentioned or remembered by their names.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And in that day I will make a covenant for IsraelWith the animals
        of the open countryAnd with the birds of the heavensAnd with the creeping
        things of the ground.And I will abolish the bow and the sword and [banish]
        war from the landAnd will make them lie down in safety.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And I will betroth you (Israel) to Me forever;Yes, I will betroth
        you to Me in righteousness and in justice,In lovingkindness and loyalty,
        and in compassion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'I will betroth you to Me in stability and in faithfulness.Then you
        will know (recognize, appreciate) the Lord [and respond with loving faithfulness].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CIt will come about in that day that I will respond,\u201D says
        the Lord.\u201CI will respond to the heavens [which ask for rain to pour
        on the earth], and they will respond to the earth [which begs for the rain],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the earth shall respond to the grain and the new wine and the
        oil [which beg it to bring them forth],And they will respond to Jezreel [My
        Israel, who will now be restored].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I will sow her for Myself in the land.I will also have mercy on her
        who had not obtained mercy;And I will say to those who were not My people,\u2018You
        are My people,\u2019And they will say, \u2018You are my God!\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hosea\u2019s Second Symbolic Marriage"
      title: "Hosea\u2019s Second Symbolic Marriage"
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to me, \u201CGo again, love a woman (Gomer)
        who is beloved by her husband and yet is an adulteress, even as the Lord
        loves the children of Israel, though they turn to other gods and love the
        raisin cakes [used in the feasts in pagan worship].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So I bought her for myself for fifteen pieces of silver and a homer
        and a half of barley [the price of a common slave]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And I said to her, \u201CYou shall stay with me for many days. You
        shall not play the prostitute nor shall you have a man; so I will also be
        toward you [until you have proved your faithfulness].\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the sons of Israel will remain for many days without king or
        prince, without sacrifice or [idolatrous] pillar, and without ephod or teraphim
        (household idols). '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Afterward the sons of Israel will return [in deep repentance] and
        seek the Lord their God and [seek from the line of] David their king [the
        King of kings\u2014the Messiah]; and they will come trembling to the Lord
        and to His goodness and blessing in the last days."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Controversy with Israel"
      title: "God\u2019s Controversy with Israel"
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear the word of the Lord, you children of Israel,For the Lord
        has a [legal] case with the inhabitants of the land,Because there is no faithfulness
        [no steadfast love, no dependability] or loyalty or kindnessOr knowledge
        of God [from personal experience with Him] in the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'There is [false] swearing of oaths, deception (broken faith), murder,
        stealing, and adultery;They employ violence, so that one [act of] bloodshed
        follows closely on another.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore the land [continually] mourns,And everyone who lives in
        it languishes [in tragic suffering]Together with the animals of the open
        country and the birds of the heavens;Even the fish of the sea disappear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Yet let no one find fault, nor let any rebuke [others];For your people
        are like those who contend with the priest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So you will stumble in the daytime,And the [false] prophet will also
        stumble with you in the night;And I will destroy your mother (Israel).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'My people are destroyed for lack of knowledge [of My law, where I
        reveal My will].Because you [the priestly nation] have rejected knowledge,I
        will also reject you from being My priest.Since you have forgotten the law
        of your God,I will also forget your children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The more they multiplied [in numbers and increased in power], the
        more they sinned against Me;I will change their glory into shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They (the priests) feed on the sin offering of My peopleAnd set their
        heart on their wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And it shall be: like people, like priest [both are wicked and both
        will be judged];So I will punish them for their waysAnd repay them for their
        deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They will eat, but not have enough;They will play the prostitute,
        but not increase [their descendants],Because they have stopped giving heed
        to the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Prostitution, wine, and new wine take away the mind and the [spiritual]
        understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "My people consult their [lifeless] wooden idol, and their [diviner\u2019s]
        wand gives them oracles.For a spirit of prostitution has led them astray
        [morally and spiritually],And they have played the prostitute, withdrawing
        themselves from their God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They sacrifice on the tops of the mountainsAnd burn incense on the
        hills,Under oaks, poplars, and terebinths,Because the shade is pleasant there.Therefore
        your daughters play the prostituteAnd your brides commit adultery.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I will not punish your daughters when they play the prostituteOr
        your brides when they commit adultery,For the men themselves slip away with
        prostitutes,And they offer sacrifices with temple prostitutes [who give their
        bodies in honor of the idol].So the people without understanding [stumble
        and fall and] come to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Though you, Israel, play the prostitute [by worshiping idols],Do
        not let Judah become guilty [of the same thing];And do not go to Gilgal [where
        idols are worshiped],Or go up to Beth-aven (House of Wickedness),Nor swear
        [oaths in idolatrous worship, saying],\u201CAs the Lord lives!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For Israel is stubborn,Like a stubborn heifer.Can the Lord now pasture
        themLike a lamb in a large field?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Ephraim is joined to idols,So let him alone [to suffer the consequences].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "When their liquor is gone [and their drinking parties are over],They
        habitually go to play the prostitute;Ephraim\u2019s rulers continue to dearly
        love shame [more than her glory which is the Lord, Israel\u2019s God].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "The wind [of God\u2019s relentless wrath] has wrapped up Israel in
        its wings,And [in captivity] they will be ashamed because of their sacrifices
        [to calves, to sun, to moon, to stars, and to pagan gods]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The People\u2019s Apostasy Rebuked"
      title: "The People\u2019s Apostasy Rebuked"
      number: 1
      content: '  Hear this and pay close attention, O priests!Give heed, O house
        of Israel!Listen, O house of the king!For the [pronounced] judgment pertains
        to you and is meant for you to hear,Because you have been a snare at MizpahAnd
        a net spread out over Tabor (military strongholds on either side of the Jordan
        River).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The revolters have gone deep into depravity,But I [the Lord God]
        will chastise them all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I know Ephraim, and Israel is not hidden from Me;For now, O Ephraim,
        you have played the prostitute and have worshiped idols;Israel has defiled
        itself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Their [immoral] practices will not permit themTo return to their
        God,For the spirit of prostitution is within themAnd they do not know the
        Lord [they do not recognize, appreciate, heed or cherish Him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the pride and self-reliance of Israel testifies against him.Therefore
        Israel, and [especially] Ephraim, stumble and fall in their wickedness and
        guilt;  Judah also has stumbled with them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They will go with their flocks and with their herdsTo seek the Lord
        [diligently searching for Him], but they will not find Him;He has withdrawn
        from them [refusing to hear the prayers of the unrepentant].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They have dealt treacherously against the Lord,For they have borne
        illegitimate (pagan) children.Now the New Moon will devour them along with
        their land [bringing judgment and captivity].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Blow the horn in Gibeah,The trumpet in Ramah [the lofty hills on
        Benjamin\u2019s northern border].Sound the alarm at Beth-aven:\u201CBehind
        you and coming after you [is the enemy], O Benjamin [be on guard]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ephraim will become a desolation in the day of rebuke;Among the tribes
        of Israel I declare what is certain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The princes of Judah are like those who move a boundary marker;I
        will pour out My wrath on them like [an unrestrained flood of] water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Ephraim is oppressed; he is broken and crushed by [divine] judgment,Because
        he was determined to follow man\u2019s command (vanities, filth, secular
        precepts).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore I am like a moth to EphraimAnd like dry rot to the house
        of Judah [in My judgment against them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When Ephraim saw his sickness,And Judah his wound,Then Ephraim went
        to Assyria [instead of the Lord]And sent to [Assyria\u2019s] great King Jareb
        [for help].But he cannot heal youNor will he cure you of your wound [received
        in judgment].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For I will be like a lion to EphraimAnd like a young lion to the
        house of Judah.I, even I, will tear to pieces and go on [tearing];I will
        carry off [the prey] and there will be no one to rescue them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: I will go away and return to My place [on high]Until they acknowledge
        their offense and bear their guilt and seek My face;In their distress they
        will earnestly seek Me, saying,
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: The Response to God\u2019s Rebuke"
      title: "The Response to God\u2019s Rebuke"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CCome and let us return [in repentance] to the Lord,For He
        has torn us, but He will heal us;He has wounded us, but He will bandage us.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'After two days He will revive us;On the third day He will raise us
        upThat we may live before Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: The Reply of the Lord'
      title: The Reply of the Lord
      number: 3
      content: "So let us know and become personally acquainted with Him; let us
        press on to know and understand fully the [greatness of the] Lord [to honor,
        heed, and deeply cherish Him].His appearing is prepared and is as certain
        as the dawn,And He will come to us [in salvation] like the [heavy] rain,Like
        the spring rain watering the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'O Ephraim, what shall I do with you?O Judah, what shall I do with
        you?For your [wavering] loyalty and kindness are [transient] like the morning
        cloudAnd like the dew that goes away early.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Therefore, I have hewn them in pieces by [the words of] the prophets;I
        have slain them by the words of My mouth;My judgments [pronounced upon them
        by the prophets] are like the light that shines forth [obvious to all].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For I desire and delight in [steadfast] loyalty [faithfulness in
        the covenant relationship], rather than sacrifice,And in the knowledge of
        God more than burnt offerings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But they, like Adam, have transgressed the covenant;There they have
        dealt treacherously against Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Gilead is a city of wrongdoers;It is tracked with bloody footprints.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And as bands of robbers [lie in] wait for a man,So a band of priests
        murder on the road toward Shechem [covering their crimes in that city of
        refuge];Certainly they have committed crimes and outrages.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I have seen a horrible thing [sins of every kind] in the house of
        Israel!Ephraim\u2019s prostitution (idolatry) is there; Israel has defiled
        itself.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Also, O Judah, there is a harvest [of divine judgment] appointed for
        you,When I restore the fortunes of My people [who have been slaves to the
        misery of sin].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ephraim\u2019s Sin"
      title: "Ephraim\u2019s Sin"
      number: 1
      content: '  When I would heal Israel,The sin (guilt) of Ephraim is uncovered,And
        the wickedness of Samaria,Because they practice false dealing;The thief enters,Bandits
        ravage and raid outside.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But they do not consider in their hearts (minds)That I remember [always]
        all their wickedness.Now their deeds surround and entangle them;They are
        before My face.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They make the king glad with their wickedness,And the princes with
        their lies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They are all adulterers;Like the heat of an ovenWhen the baker ceases
        to stir the fire, [their passion smolders]From the kneading of the dough
        until it is leavened.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'On the [special] day of our king, the princes became sick with the
        heat of wine;The king stretched out his hand [in association] with scoffers
        (lawless people).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'As they approach their plotting,Their mind burns [with intrigue]
        like an oven [while they lie in wait].Their anger smolders all night;In the
        morning it blazes like a flaming fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They are all hot like an ovenAnd they consume their judges (rulers);All
        their kings have fallen.There is no one among them who calls to Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ephraim mixes himself with the [Gentile] nations [seeking favor with
        one country, then another];Ephraim is a cake not turned [worthless; ready
        to be thrown away].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Strangers have devoured his strength,Yet he does not know it;Gray
        hairs are sprinkled on him,Yet he does not know.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Though the pride of Israel testifies against him,Yet they do not
        return [in repentance] to the Lord their God,Nor seek nor search for nor
        desire Him [as essential] in spite of all this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ephraim also is like a silly dove, without heart or good sense;They
        call to Egypt [for help], they go to Assyria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When they go, I will spread My net over them;I will bring them down
        like birds of the heavens [into Assyrian captivity].I will chastise them
        in accordance with the proclamation (prophecy) to their congregation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to them, for they have wandered away from
        Me!Devastation is theirs, because they have rebelled and trespassed against
        Me!I would redeem them, but they speak lies against Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They do not cry out to Me from their heartWhen they wail on their
        beds [in unbelieving despair];For the sake of grain and new wine they assemble
        themselves [as if worshiping Baal];They rebel against Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Although I trained and strengthened their arms [for victory over
        their enemies],Yet they devise evil against Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: They turn, but they do not turn upward to the Most High.They are like
        a poorly crafted bow [that misses the mark];Their princes shall fall by the
        swordBecause of the insolence of their tongue.This will be cause for their
        mockery and disdain in the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Reaps the Whirlwind'
      title: Israel Reaps the Whirlwind
      number: 1
      content: '  Set the trumpet to your lips [announcing impending judgment]!Like
        a [great] vulture the enemy comes against the house of the Lord,Because they
        have broken My covenantAnd transgressed and rebelled against My law.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then they will cry out to Me,\u201CMy God, we of Israel know You!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Israel has rejected the good;The enemy shall pursue him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They set up kings, but not from Me [therefore without My blessing];They
        have appointed princes, but I did not know it.With their silver and their
        gold they made idols for themselves,That they might be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He has rejected your [pagan] calf, O Samaria, saying,\u201CMy wrath
        burns against them.\u201DHow long will they be incapable of innocence?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For even this [loathsome calf] is from Israel.A craftsman made it,
        so it is not God;Surely the calf of Samaria will be broken to pieces and
        go up in flames.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For they sow the wind [in evil]And they reap the whirlwind [in disaster].The
        standing grain has no growth;It yields no grain.If it were to yield, strangers
        would swallow it up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Israel is [as if] swallowed up [by enemies];They are now among the
        nationsLike a vessel [of cheap, coarse pottery] that is useless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For they have gone up to Assyria,Like a wild donkey wandering alone
        and taking her own way;Ephraim has hired lovers (pagan allies).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Yes, even though [with presents] they hire allies among the nations,Now
        I will gather them up;And [in a little while] they will begin to grow weak
        and diminishBecause of the burden imposed by the king of princes [the king
        of Assyria].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For Ephraim has constructed many altars for sin;They are altars intended
        for sinning [which multiply his guilt].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I wrote for him the ten thousand precepts of My law,But they are
        regarded as a strange thing [which does not concern him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'As for My sacrificial offerings,They sacrifice the meat [as a mere
        formality] and eat it,But the Lord is not pleased with them and does not
        accept them.Now He will remember and take into account their wickedness and
        guilt,And punish them for their sins.They will return [in captivity] to [another]
        Egypt [that is, Assyria].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: For Israel has forgotten his Maker and built palaces [and pagan temples],And
        Judah has built many fortified cities;But I will send a fire upon their cities
        so that it may consume their palaces and fortresses.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ephraim Punished'
      title: Ephraim Punished
      number: 1
      content: "  Do not rejoice, O Israel, with exultation as do the [pagan] peoples,For
        you have played the prostitute, turning away from your God.You have loved
        prostitutes\u2019 earnings on every threshing floor [attributing the harvest
        to the Baals instead of to God].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The threshing floor and the wine press will no longer feed them,And
        the new wine will fail them [because they failed to honor the God who provides].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'They will not remain in the land of the Lord,But Ephraim will return
        to [another] Egypt [in bondage]And they will eat [ceremonially] unclean food
        in Assyria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They will not pour out drink offerings of wine to the Lord;Their
        sacrifices will not please Him.  Their bread will be like mourners\u2019
        bread [eaten at funerals];All who eat it will be [ceremonially] unclean,For
        their bread will be for themselves;It will not enter the house of the Lord
        [to be consecrated].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'What will you do on the day of the appointed festivalAnd on the day
        of the feast of the Lord [when you are in exile]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For behold, they will go away because of devastation and destruction;Egypt
        will gather them up, Memphis will bury them.Weeds will take over their treasures
        of silver;Thorns will grow in their tents.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The days of punishment have come;The days of retribution are at hand;Let
        Israel know this!The prophet is [considered] a fool;The man [of God] who
        is inspired is [treated as if] demented,Because of the abundance of your
        wickedness and guilt,And because your deep antagonism [toward God and the
        prophets] is so great.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Ephraim was a watchman with my God, a [true] prophet [to warn the
        nation];But the snare of a bird catcher was laid in all his paths.And there
        is only deep hostility in the house of his God (the land of Israel).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They have deeply corrupted (perverted) themselvesAs in the days of
        Gibeah.The Lord will remember their wickedness and guilt;He will punish their
        sins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I found Israel like grapes in the wilderness [an unexpected and refreshing
        delight];I saw your fathers (ancestors) as the first ripe fruit on the fig
        tree in its first season,But they came to Baal-peor and consecrated themselves
        to shamefulness [the worship of Baal],And [because of their spiritual and
        physical adultery] they became as detestable and loathsome as the thing they
        loved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'As for Ephraim, their glory will fly away like a bird;No birth, no
        pregnancy, and [because of their impurity] no conception.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Even though they bring up their children,Yet I will bereave them
        until not one is left.Indeed, woe (judgment is coming) to them when I look
        away and withdraw [My blessing] from them!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ephraim, as I have seen,Is planted in a pleasant [and prosperous]
        meadow like Tyre;But Ephraim will bring out his children to the executioner
        [for slaughter].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Give them [the punishment they deserve], O Lord! What will You give?Give
        them a miscarrying womb and dry breasts.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'All their wickedness [says the Lord] is focused in Gilgal;Indeed,
        I came to hate them there!Because of the wickedness of their [idolatrous]
        practicesI will drive them out of My house (the land of Israel)!I will love
        them no longer;All their princes are rebels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Ephraim is stricken, their root is dried up,They will bear no fruit.Even
        though they give birth,I will slay the precious children of their womb.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: My God will reject them and cast them awayBecause they did not listen
        to Him;And they will be wanderers (fugitives) among the nations.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Retribution for Israel\u2019s Sin"
      title: "Retribution for Israel\u2019s Sin"
      number: 1
      content: '  Israel is a luxuriant and prolific vine;He produces fruit for himself.The
        more his fruit,The more altars he made [to Baal];The richer his land,The
        better he made the [idolatrous] pillars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Their heart is divided (faithless);Now they must bear their guilt
        and punishment.The Lord will break down [the horns of] their altars;He will
        destroy their idolatrous pillars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Surely now they will say [in despair], \u201CWe have no [true] king,For
        we do not revere the Lord;And as for the king, what can he do for us [to
        rescue us]?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'They have spoken empty (disingenuous) words,Swearing falsely to make
        covenants [they intend to break];Therefore, judgment springs up like poisonous
        weeds in the furrows of the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The people of Samaria will fear and trembleFor the [idolatrous] calf
        of Beth-aven (House of Wickedness).Indeed, its people will mourn over itAnd
        its idolatrous priests will cry out and wail over it,Over its glory, because
        the glory [of their calf god] has departed from it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The golden calf itself will be carried to AssyriaAs tribute to King
        Jareb;Ephraim will be seized with shameAnd Israel will be ashamed of his
        own counsel [to worship the calf and separate Israel from Judah].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'As for Samaria, her king will be cut off and float awayLike a twig
        on the surface of the water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Also the high places of Aven (Beth-aven), the sin of Israel, will
        be destroyed;The thorn and the thistle will grow on their [pagan] altars,And
        [in despair] they will say to the mountains,\u201CCover us!\u201D And to
        the hills, \u201CFall on us!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'O Israel, you have [willfully] sinned since the days of Gibeah;There
        they (Israel) stand!Will not the battle against the sons of wickedness overtake
        them at Gibeah?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'When it is my desire [to defend My righteousness], I will chastise
        them;And [hostile] peoples will be gathered against themWhen they are bound
        and punished for their double guilt [their revolt against the Lord and their
        worship of idols].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ephraim is a trained heifer that loves to tread out the grain,But
        I will come over her fair neck with a heavy yoke [for hard field work].I
        will harness Ephraim;Judah will plow and Jacob will harrow and rake for himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Sow with a view to righteousness [that righteousness, like seed,
        may germinate];Reap in accordance with mercy and lovingkindness.Break up
        your uncultivated ground,For it is time to seek and search diligently for
        the Lord [and to long for His blessing]Until He comes to rain righteousness
        and His gift of salvation on you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You have plowed and planted wickedness, you have reaped the [willful]
        injustice [of oppressors],You have eaten the fruit of lies.Because you have
        trusted in your own way and your chariots, and in your many warriors,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore an uproar will arise among your people,And all your fortresses
        will be destroyed,As Shalman destroyed Beth-arbel on the day of battle,When
        mothers were dashed in pieces with their children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: In this way it will be done to you at [idolatrous] Bethel because
        of your great wickedness;At daybreak the king of Israel will be completely
        cut off.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God is the Loving Father of His People'
      title: God is the Loving Father of His People
      number: 1
      content: '  When Israel was a child [a young nation], I loved him,And I called
        My son out of Egypt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The more they [the prophets] called them [to repentance and obedience],The
        more they went away from them;They kept sacrificing to the BaalsAnd burning
        incense to the carved images.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Yet it is I who taught Ephraim to walk,Taking them in My arms [nurturing
        the young nation];But they did not know that I healed them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I led them gently with cords of a man, with bonds of love [guiding
        them],And I was to them as one who lifts up and eases the yoke [of the law]
        over their jaws;And I bent down to them and fed them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They will not return to the land of Egypt,But Assyria will be their
        king [bringing them into captivity]Because they refused to return to Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sword will whirl against and fall on their cities,And will demolish
        the bars of their gates and fortificationsAnd will consume them because of
        their counsels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'My people are bent on turning from Me;Though the prophets call them
        to the One on high,None at all exalts Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'How can I give you up, O Ephraim?How can I surrender you, O Israel?How
        can I make you like Admah?How can I treat you like Zeboiim?My heart recoils
        within Me;All My compassions are kindled together [for My nation of Israel].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will not execute the fierceness of My anger;I will not return to
        Ephraim to destroy him again.For I am God and not man, the Holy One in your
        midst [who will not revoke My covenant],And I will not come in wrath or enter
        the city [in judgment].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They will walk after the Lord [in obedience and worship],Who will
        roar like a lion;He will roar [summoning them]And His sons will come trembling
        from the west.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They will come trembling and hurriedly like birds from EgyptAnd like
        doves from the land of Assyria;And I will settle them in their houses [in
        the land of their inheritance], declares the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Ephraim surrounds Me with liesAnd the house of Israel with deceit;Judah
        is also unruly against God,Even against the faithful Holy One.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ephraim Reminded'
      title: Ephraim Reminded
      number: 1
      content: '  Ephraim feeds on the [emptiness of the] windAnd [continually] pursues
        the [parching] east wind [which brings destruction];Every day he multiplies
        lies and violence.Further, he makes a covenant with AssyriaAnd (olive) oil
        is carried to Egypt [to seek alliances].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord also has a dispute [a legal complaint and an indictment]
        with Judah,And He will punish Jacob in accordance with his ways;He will repay
        him in accordance with his deeds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "In their mother\u2019s womb he took his brother by the heel,And in
        his maturity he contended with God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He wrestled with the angel and prevailed;He wept [in repentance]
        and sought His favor.He met Him at BethelAnd there God spoke with [him and
        through him with] us\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Even the Lord, the God of hosts,The name of Him [who spoke with Jacob]
        is the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Therefore, return [in repentance] to your God,Observe and highly
        regard kindness and justice,And wait [expectantly] for your God continually.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'A merchant, in whose hand are false and fraudulent balances;He loves
        to oppress and exploit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Ephraim said, \u201CI have indeed become rich [and powerful as a
        nation];I have found wealth for myself.In all my labors they will not find
        in meAny wickedness that would be sin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But I have been the Lord your God since [you became a nation in]
        the land of Egypt;I will make you live in tents again,As in the days of the
        appointed and solemn festival.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I have also spoken to [you through] the prophets,And I gave [them]
        many visions [to make My will known],And through the prophets I gave parables
        [to appeal to your sense of right and wrong].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Is there wickedness (idolatry) in Gilead?Surely the people there
        are worthless.In Gilgal [they defy Me when] they sacrifice bulls,Yes, [after
        My judgment] their [pagan] altars are like the stone heapsIn the furrows
        of the fields.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now Jacob (Israel) fled into the open country of Aram (Paddan-aram),And
        [there] Israel (Jacob) worked and served for a wife,And for a wife he kept
        sheep.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And by a prophet (Moses) the Lord brought Israel up from Egypt,And
        by a prophet Israel was preserved.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: Ephraim has provoked most bitter anger;So his Lord will leave his
        bloodguilt on him [invoking punishment]And bring back to him his shame and
        dishonor.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ephraim\u2019s Idolatry"
      title: "Ephraim\u2019s Idolatry"
      number: 1
      content: "  When Ephraim spoke, there was trembling and terror.He exalted himself
        [above the other tribes] in Israel;But through [the worship of] Baal he became
        guilty and died [spiritually, and then came ruin, sealing Israel\u2019s doom
        as a nation].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And now they sin more and more,And make for themselves molten images,Idols
        skillfully made from their silver [as it pleased them],All of them the work
        of the craftsmen.They say of these [very works of their hands], \u201CLet
        those who sacrifice kiss and show respect to the calves [as if they were
        living gods]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Therefore they will be [swiftly dissipated] like the morning cloudOr
        like dew which soon disappears,Like chaff which swirls with the whirlwind
        from the threshing floor,And like smoke from the chimney or through the window
        [worthless and without substance \u2014they will vanish].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Yet I have been the Lord your GodSince [the time you became a nation
        in] the land of Egypt;And you were not to know any god except Me,For there
        is no savior besides Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I knew and regarded you and cared for you in the wilderness,In the
        land of drought.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'When they had their pasture, they became satisfied,And being satisfied,
        their heart became proud (self-centered);Therefore they forgot Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'So I will be like a lion to them;Like a leopard I will watch and
        lie in wait [ready to attack] by the road [to Assyria].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I will encounter them like a bear robbed of her cubs,And I will tear
        open their chests;There I will also devour them like a lioness,As a wild
        beast would tear them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'It is your destruction, O Israel,Because you are against Me, [and
        have rebelled] against your help.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Where now is your kingThat he may save you [when you are attacked]
        in all your cities?And your judges of whom you asked,\u201CGive me a king
        and princes\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I gave you a king in My anger,And I took him away in My wrath [as
        punishment].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The wickedness of Ephraim [which is not yet completely punished]
        is bound up [as in a bag];His sin is stored up [for judgment and destruction].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The pains of childbirth come on him;But he is not a wise son,For
        it is not the time to delay [his chance at a new birth] as the womb opens
        [but he ignores the opportunity to change].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Shall I ransom them from the power of Sheol (the place of the dead)?Shall
        I redeem them from death?  O death, where are your thorns?O Sheol, where
        is your sting?Compassion is hidden from My eyes [because of their failure
        to repent].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For though he flourishes among the reeds (his fellow tribes),An east
        wind (Assyria) will come,The breath of the Lord rising from the desert;And
        Ephraim\u2019s spring will become dryAnd his fountain will be dried up.Assyria
        will plunder his treasury of every precious object.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: Samaria will be found guilty [and become desolate],Because she rebelled
        against her God;They will fall by the sword,Their infants will be dashed
        in pieces,And their pregnant women will be ripped open.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Future Blessing"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Future Blessing"
      number: 1
      content: '  O Israel, return [in repentance] to the Lord your God,For you have
        stumbled and fallen [visited by tragedy], because of your sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Take the words [confessing your guilt] with you and return to the
        Lord.Say to Him, \u201CTake away all our wickedness;Accept what is good and
        receive us graciously,So that we may present the fruit of our lips (gratitude).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Assyria will not save us;We will not ride on horses [relying on military
        might],Nor will we say again to [the idols who are] the work of our hands,\u2018You
        are our gods.\u2019For in You [O Lord] the orphan finds love and compassion
        and mercy.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I will heal their apostasy and faithlessness;I will love them freely,For
        My anger has turned away from Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I shall be like the dew to Israel;He will blossom like the lily,And
        he will take root like the cedars of Lebanon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'His shoots will sprout,And his beauty will be like the olive treeAnd
        his fragrance like the cedars of Lebanon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Those who live in his shadowWill again raise grain,And they will
        blossom like the vine.His renown will be like the wine of Lebanon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'O Ephraim, what more have I to do with idols?It is I who have answered
        and will care for you and watch over you.I am like a luxuriant cypress tree;With
        Me your fruit is found [which is to nourish you].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: Whoever is [spiritually] wise, let him understand these things;  Whoever
        is [spiritually] discerning and understanding, let him know them.For the
        ways of the Lord are right,And the righteous will walk in them,But transgressors
        will stumble and fall in them.
      comments: []
